aks\\.',\n    'No clean contradiction in treble either: your data were not aimed at quasi-anechoic HF/directivity verification\\.',\n    'The two datasets mostly talk about different layers of the system: speaker voicing vs\\. room response\\.',\n    'Common point: both external reviews describe the speaker as somewhat bright / uneven in upper mids-treble\\.',\n    'Most likely combined picture: decent drivers, compromised crossover, then strong room effects on top\\.',\n\\]\nmod_items = \\[\n    'Mod 0 is the safest first experiment: only tweeter attenuation, no irreversible rebuild\\.',\n    'It may help if you hear too much brilliance, sizzle or detached tweeter energy\\.',\n    'It will not solve the current main issue in your room: LF peaks, decay and L/R asymmetry\\.',\n    'Full crossover mods 1 / 1\\.5 / 2 target the known system integration problem more deeply\\.',\n    'For you, those deeper mods only make sense after placement tests or if HF character still annoys you\\.',\n\\]\n\ndraw_bullets\\(118, 245, ext_items, txt, colors\\['gold'\\], 610\\)\ndraw_bullets\\(873, 245, meas_items, txt, colors\\['blue'\\], 610\\)\ndraw_bullets\\(118, 630, agree_items, txt, colors\\['rose'\\], 610\\)\ndraw_bullets\\(873, 630, mod_items, txt, colors\\['green'\\], 610\\)\n\nd\\.text\\(\\(118, 495\\), 'AudioExcite is broadly positive about hardware quality, but critical of the minimalist crossover\\.', font=small, fill=muted\\)\nd\\.text\\(\\(873, 495\\), 'Your measurements mainly describe room interaction, not clean quasi-anechoic speaker behavior\\.', font=small, fill=muted\\)\n\nd\\.rounded_rectangle\\(\\(118, 950, 777, 1060\\), radius=14, fill='#fff9fb', outline='#d7bec6', width=2\\)\nd\\.text\\(\\(142, 974\\), 'Working interpretation for your setup:', font=bold, fill=colors\\['rose'\\]\\)\nfor i, line in enumerate\\(wrap\\(d, 'At home the room dominates below ~150 Hz, but the speaker itself may still be adding a mild HF voicing issue above the modal region\\.', txt, 600\\)\\):\n    d\\.text\\(\\(142, 1008 \\+ i\\*29\\), line, font=txt, fill=text\\)\n\nd\\.rounded_rectangle\\(\\(873, 950, 1532, 1070\\), radius=14, fill='#f8fff8', outline='#c6dcc8', width=2\\)\nd\\.text\\(\\(898, 974\\), 'Recommended order:', font=bold, fill=colors\\['green'\\]\\)\nfor i, line in enumerate\\(wrap\\(d, '1\\) placement and symmetry, 2\\) optional Mod 0, 3\\) only then consider full crossover rebuild\\.', txt, 600\\)\\):\n    d\\.text\\(\\(898, 1008 \\+ i\\*29\\), line, font=txt, fill=text\\)\nfor i, line in enumerate\\(wrap\\(d, 'Reason: crossover mod can improve tonality/coherence, but cannot remove room modes\\.', txt, 600\\)\\):\n    d\\.text\\(\\(898, 1038 \\+ i\\*29\\), line, font=txt, fill=text\\)\n\nd\\.text\\(\\(95, 1145\\), 'Sources summarized: AudioExcite parts 1-4, ASR forum thread, and Home REW documentation\\.', font=small, fill=muted\\)\nimg\\.save\\(out, quality=95\\)\nprint\\(out\\)\nPY$/": {
